        <div class="description">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Campus Life</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            The college provides B.Sc. programs in Electrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE), Civil Engineering (CE), and Computer Science and Engineering (CSE), each accommodating 63 students. With modern infrastructure and comprehensive facilities, the college ensures a conducive environment for academic and personal growth. <br>
            It is located on a 12-acre campus with 10 buildings, including academic blocks, an administrative building, a library, an auditorium, a cafeteria, and facilities like a bank and post office. The college offers residential accommodations for students: two male halls (160 capacity each) named Bongobondhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Hall and Palli Kabi Jasimuddin Hall, and a female hall with a capacity of 96.
          </p>
